<HEADLINE>
Vienna ex-mayor to visit Havel, discuss allegations of spying
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
PRAGUE, Czech Republic (AP) _ The ex mayor of Vienna is expected
to meet <TIMEX2 val="1998-W50" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">next week</TIMEX2> with President Vaclav Havel to discuss
allegations of the Austrian's collaboration with the police under
the <TIMEX2 val="PAST_REF" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="1998-12-04T05:08:00" anchor_dir="BEFORE" comment="">past</TIMEX2> communist regime, the <TIMEX2 val="XXXX-XX-XX" mod="" set="YES" non_specific="YES" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">daily</TIMEX2> Pravo reported <TIMEX2 val="1998-12-04" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">Friday</TIMEX2>.
According to Havel's spokesman Ladislav Spacek, Havel issued the
invitation to <TIMEX2 val="PAST_REF" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="1998-12-04T05:08:00" anchor_dir="BEFORE" comment="">former</TIMEX2> Mayor Helmut Zilk <TIMEX2 val="1998-12-03" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">Thursday</TIMEX2>, but no specific
date was announced.
Zilk was rejected for a Czech Republic medal of honor just <TIMEX2 val="1998-10-25" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">three
days before the official ceremony on <TIMEX2 val="1998-10-28" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">Oct 28</TIMEX2></TIMEX2>, because of sudden
allegations that he was an informant for police in communist
Czechoslovakia.
Havel's office then cited newspaper reports and other
unspecified information supposedly confirming the allegations. By
law, Havel has no official access to the communist police files.
Zilk, 71, denied the allegations as ``absolute nonsense''.
According to Spacek, Havel was briefed <TIMEX2 val="1998-12-03" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">Thursday</TIMEX2> on the contents
of Zilk's file by Interior minister Vaclav Grulich and archive
manager Jan Frolik.
</TEXT>
